'''Kwesi sar Mashewe''' and her sister [[Inshula sar Mashewe]] were huntswomen and bounty hunters active in the late 14{{th}} century [[DR]].

{{quote|''That is all they trust of us Tashalar - our [[wine]]s and our hunting. I would be out there myself, save for a wound in my leg
that must first heal. So while I rest, they have hired me to examine the kills of bounty hunters, to make sure they are legal.''|Kwesi sar Mashewe}}
